Known issues:------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |   RetroDaBox has no hitbox, uses last hitbox used.  URGENT!!!  |-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Maybe use same hitbox as regular DaBox?Characters with falling speed > 1.0 will vibrate.  Needs fixing?  Falling speed doesn't seem to have any noticeable effect on actual falling speed?Variable 'Falling?' doesn't seem to be read anywhere but set in a lot of places?Why set 'Falling?' to 6?  A question mark implies a boolean value, like 1 or 0, nothing else.  But we set it to 6 in a lot of places, add 1 to it, and then set it back to 1 or 0 without ever reading it as far as I can tell.Issues fixed:Started making Powerups less laggy via reducing the amount of powerups spawned from crates.Fixed Fish Stickman's walk cycyle not animating due to only two frames. I just added two extra frames for now but there may be a better, more efficieint way.Added 2 new maps: Kitchen and Sketchpad :DBalanced out some fighters to make some of them less overpowered.Todo:Do something about COM projectile.  Maybe use a separate projectile sprite for P1 but a combined one for COM and P2 since those two never need to be distinguished.Further investigate power up lag.Make it so player 1's projectiles don't damage said player, maybe making them into seperate each projectile into differant sprites like we talked about?Add back the Triple Shot attack ( X + V)Work on Player 2 a bit once Player 1 is as smooth as butter :)
